universe of origin : the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored
seal               : The Wii U paired a modest tri-core PowerPC and an AMD GPU with its real idea: a tablet-like GamePad with a built-in touchscreen for off-TV and second-screen play. Confusing marketing and weak sales made it a commercial failure — yet its core concept was vindicated, scaled up, by the Switch.
